<p class="ql-align-justify"><strong>在美国创办小企业简便易行</strong></p>
<p class="ql-align-justify">November is designated as National Entrepreneurship Month in the United States, a time to celebrate the entrepreneurs who serve their communities and bolster the economy. </p>
<p class="ql-align-justify">Starting and registering a new business in the United States takes an average of just four days, says the World Bank’s Doing Business report for 2020.</p>
<p class="ql-align-justify">There are 30.7 million businesses in the United States, and 99 percent of them are small businesses, according to the U.S. Small Business Administration’s Office of Advocacy. (The U.S. Small Business Administration (SBA) defines small as having fewer than 500 employees.)</p>
<p class="ql-align-justify">The ease of starting a business is one reason entrepreneurship is the backbone of the U.S. economy. The SBA’s 2019 data estimates that small businesses employ 59 million workers — 48 percent of the U.S. workforce. </p>
